text: Warren Anthony Wisneski (born 19 February 1969 in New Plymouth, Taranaki) is a retired New Zealand cricketer who played three one-day internationals in 2000 but no tests. He also played for Central Districts and Canterbury in the Plunket Shield before retiring after the 2003/04 season. ==Other websites== * Category:1969 births Category:Living people Category:New Zealand cricketers Category:People from New Plymouth
